    <COMMIT>
      <MESSAGE>Added Clickable hostname on status page. #1221 This should fully implement #1221 by modifying the API to return the URL of the monitor as well. In order to link only to HTTP monitors, the URL is checked to see if it is blank or https:// (the default). If so no link is included. The reason I implemented it like this instead of just sending the monitor type with the API is because I want to limit the amount of extra data we send to the client and the monitor type seemed unneccesary. Note: this could lead to issues where a user changes a monitor type from HTTP to another non HTTP type but I belive that this is acceptable as there are only a limited number of circumstances where this might occur. Signed-off-by: Matthew Nickson &lt;mnickson@sidingsmedia.com&gt;</MESSAGE>
      <SHA>1febf4ede9c951e6c0e85052cfc5ba8cfee2b645</SHA>
      <PATCHEDFILES>
        <FILE>server/model/monitor.js</FILE>
        <FILE>src/components/PublicGroupList.vue</FILE>
      </PATCHEDFILES>
    </COMMIT>
    <COMMIT>
      <MESSAGE>Added Clickable hostname on status page. #1221 This should fully implement #1221 by modifying the API and adding two new properties to the result. The `sendUrl` property denotes if the URL is sent and `url` is included when required. Client side checks have been implemented in order to only show a link when the URL is vaugely correct. I.e not &quot;&quot; or &quot;https://&quot;. This prevents the link from being included if the monitor type is not HTTP without having to publicly expose the monitor type. The exposure of the URL is configuarable for each monitor on each status page by clicking on the link icon. Signed-off-by: Matthew Nickson &lt;mnickson@sidingsmedia.com&gt;</MESSAGE>
